## Third-party source material

Some lessons derive from external educational material (Stanford lectures,
open-source documentation, published cheatsheets). These sources retain their
own licenses and are credited in each lesson's `references.mdx` per the
attribution policy in `Doc/attribution-policy.md`.

Examples currently in use or planned:

- **Stanford CME 295 cheatsheet** by Afshine & Shervine Amidi — MIT License.
  See [afshinea/stanford-cme-295-transformers-large-language-models](https://github.com/afshinea/stanford-cme-295-transformers-large-language-models).

Per the attribution policy, derivative lessons include the source license
notice in their `references.mdx` file.
